*Umreti* je neizbežan deo života. (To die is an inevitable part of life.)

Kad je videla kako se njen deda *umirao*, nekako se osećala izgubljeno. (When she saw her grandfather *dying*, she felt somehow lost.)

Niko nije mogao da spreči njegovu *smrt*. (Nobody could prevent his *death*.)

Ponekad se čini da je njen život *umro* pre nego što je počeo. (Sometimes it seems like her life *died* before it even started.)

*Umiranje* je proces koji se odvija u trenutku. (*Dying* is a process that takes place in an instant.)